{
    "publish_date": "2012-08-16T13:35:42.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT7M4S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "DR. JAMES GRIME: Yeah, I&#39;m going\nto tell you a story, but", 
            "dur": "2.1", 
            "start": "0.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "what I thought I&#39;d start with\nis a little puzzle.", 
            "dur": "3.99", 
            "start": "2.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then while people are\nthinking about the puzzle,", 
            "dur": "2.05", 
            "start": "6.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;ll tell you a little story,\none of the big legends of", 
            "dur": "2.44", 
            "start": "8.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "mathematics.", 
            "dur": "0.55", 
            "start": "11.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then we&#39;ll see what the\nanswer to the puzzle was.", 
            "dur": "2.35", 
            "start": "11.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The puzzle is fairly\neasy to state.", 
            "dur": "3.2", 
            "start": "13.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I just want you to add up the\ndigits from 1 to 1 million.", 
            "dur": "4.45", 
            "start": "17.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now I want you to add\nup all the digits--", 
            "dur": "2.25", 
            "start": "21.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "if you imagine you&#39;ve\nwrote out the", 
            "dur": "1.54", 
            "start": "23.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "numbers 1 to 1 million.", 
            "dur": "1.79", 
            "start": "25.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I want you to add up all the\ndigits, not the numbers.", 
            "dur": "3.16", 
            "start": "27.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if I want to say 123\nplus 124, that&#39;s not", 
            "dur": "4.32", 
            "start": "30.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "what I want to do.", 
            "dur": "1.22", 
            "start": "34.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I want to add up all the digits\nof those numbers, 1", 
            "dur": "4.58", 
            "start": "35.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "plus 2 plus 3 plus\n1 plus 2 plus 4.", 
            "dur": "4.73", 
            "start": "40.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Imagine writing a list of all\nthe numbers from 1 to 1", 
            "dur": "2.92", 
            "start": "45.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "million with all those digits,\nand I want you to add up all", 
            "dur": "4.13", 
            "start": "48.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the digits.", 
            "dur": "0.45", 
            "start": "52.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And what answer will you get?", 
            "dur": "2.89", 
            "start": "52.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "While you think about that, I&#39;m\ngoing to tell you one of", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "55.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "these famous mathematical\nstories.", 
            "dur": "3.25", 
            "start": "57.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So this is the story of Gauss.", 
            "dur": "1.76", 
            "start": "61.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Carl Gauss.", 
            "dur": "1.36", 
            "start": "62.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Carl Gauss is possibly one of\nthe greatest mathematicians of", 
            "dur": "4.6", 
            "start": "64.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the last few hundred years.", 
            "dur": "1.38", 
            "start": "68.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He really is a really\nlarge figure.", 
            "dur": "2.81", 
            "start": "70.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now the story goes that when\nhe was nine, he started to", 
            "dur": "4.02", 
            "start": "73.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "attend, at school, his\narithmetic class.", 
            "dur": "3.71", 
            "start": "77.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now arithmetic class would\ninclude lots of boys, all the", 
            "dur": "4.88", 
            "start": "80.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "way up to the age of 15.", 
            "dur": "1.89", 
            "start": "85.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Imagine, right?", 
            "dur": "0.82", 
            "start": "87.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is 1780 we&#39;re talking\nabout, a long time ago.", 
            "dur": "3.76", 
            "start": "88.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Imagine it&#39;s a drab schoolroom,\nand it&#39;s very", 
            "dur": "4.29", 
            "start": "92.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "worn, and the floor\nwas uneven.", 
            "dur": "3.67", 
            "start": "96.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the teacher was also drab\nand worn and uneven himself.", 
            "dur": "5.58", 
            "start": "100.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Apparently he was\nquite a bully.", 
            "dur": "2.52", 
            "start": "105.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He would walk around with\nhis cane and he", 
            "dur": "2.29", 
            "start": "108.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "would thrash the boys.", 
            "dur": "1.87", 
            "start": "110.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now one day, to keep\nthem quiet--", 
            "dur": "3.16", 
            "start": "112.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "yeah, this&#39;ll keep &#39;em\nquiet for an hour--", 
            "dur": "2.02", 
            "start": "115.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "he gave them a problem--", 
            "dur": "1.34", 
            "start": "117.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to add up all the numbers\nfrom 1 to 100.", 
            "dur": "3.57", 
            "start": "118.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So add up all the numbers\nfrom 1 to 100.", 
            "dur": "2.825", 
            "start": "122.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So 1 plus 2 plus\n3 plus 4 plus--", 
            "dur": "5.005", 
            "start": "125.235"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "all the way up to 100.", 
            "dur": "3.01", 
            "start": "130.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That was the problem\nhe gave the pupils.", 
            "dur": "2.42", 
            "start": "133.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And they had to write on\nslates in those days.", 
            "dur": "2.69", 
            "start": "135.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And when you got the solution,\nyou would put your slate on", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "138.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the teacher&#39;s table.", 
            "dur": "1.17", 
            "start": "141.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now Gauss, when he was given\nthis problem, immediately", 
            "dur": "4.28", 
            "start": "142.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "threw his slate onto\nthe teacher&#39;s", 
            "dur": "1.95", 
            "start": "146.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "table with an answer.", 
            "dur": "2.33", 
            "start": "148.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now the other boys continued\ntheir work, adding up all the", 
            "dur": "3.34", 
            "start": "151.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "numbers, multiplying and\nadding and subtracting,", 
            "dur": "2.38", 
            "start": "154.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "whatever they had to do.", 
            "dur": "1.89", 
            "start": "156.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This brute of a teacher strolled\naround the classroom,", 
            "dur": "5.3", 
            "start": "158.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "throwing just pitying looks at\npoor Gauss, this guessing the", 
            "dur": "3.73", 
            "start": "164"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "answer and throwing\nit onto the table.", 
            "dur": "1.82", 
            "start": "167.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When the hour was over, he\ntook the stack of slates,", 
            "dur": "5.47", 
            "start": "169.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "turned them over so that Gauss&#39;s\nanswer was on the top,", 
            "dur": "3.11", 
            "start": "175.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and read out the answer.", 
            "dur": "1.5", 
            "start": "178.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To his astonishment, he\ngot the answer right.", 
            "dur": "3.05", 
            "start": "179.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The answer is 5,050.", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "182.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Which meant that Gauss was able\nto solve it in seconds.", 
            "dur": "3.73", 
            "start": "185.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How did he solve it?", 
            "dur": "1.03", 
            "start": "188.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, he had a trick.", 
            "dur": "1.97", 
            "start": "189.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The trick was, he noticed\nthat if you add", 
            "dur": "2.54", 
            "start": "191.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the numbers in pairs--", 
            "dur": "1.31", 
            "start": "194.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m going to start with 1 and\nI&#39;m going to add it to 100.", 
            "dur": "5.09", 
            "start": "195.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What you get is 101.", 
            "dur": "3.26", 
            "start": "200.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now if you take the second\nnumber and add it to the", 
            "dur": "2.55", 
            "start": "204.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "second to last number,\n99, you get 101.", 
            "dur": "4.75", 
            "start": "206.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You take 3 and add it\nto 98, you get 101.", 
            "dur": "4.52", 
            "start": "211.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, each pair that\nyou make in this", 
            "dur": "2.72", 
            "start": "215.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "way would equal 101.", 
            "dur": "2.42", 
            "start": "218.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How many pairs do you make?", 
            "dur": "2.01", 
            "start": "220.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, there&#39;s 100 there.", 
            "dur": "2.16", 
            "start": "222.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "50 pairs, you make.", 
            "dur": "1.32", 
            "start": "225.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So he just took 101\nand timesed it by", 
            "dur": "2.44", 
            "start": "226.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "50, and he got 5,050.", 
            "dur": "3.65", 
            "start": "228.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So this story was first written\nabout in an obituary", 
            "dur": "4.27", 
            "start": "232.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by one of Carl Gauss&#39;s\nfriends.", 
            "dur": "2.03", 
            "start": "236.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Apparently, Carl Gauss would\ntell this story himself.", 
            "dur": "2.95", 
            "start": "238.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So it seems to be fairly true.", 
            "dur": "3.35", 
            "start": "241.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Some embellishments over\nthe years have been the", 
            "dur": "2.79", 
            "start": "245.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "brutishness of this\nteacher, with this", 
            "dur": "2.58", 
            "start": "247.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "cane and his thrashing.", 
            "dur": "1.7", 
            "start": "250.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s been added onto\nover the years.", 
            "dur": "2.64", 
            "start": "252.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The problem I gave you about\nadding the numbers 1 to 100,", 
            "dur": "4.49", 
            "start": "254.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that&#39;s been added onto over\nthe years, as well.", 
            "dur": "3.29", 
            "start": "259.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We don&#39;t know what the\noriginal problem was.", 
            "dur": "2.735", 
            "start": "262.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So to finish our puzzle\nnow, maybe", 
            "dur": "2.815", 
            "start": "265.385"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you&#39;ve got time to think.", 
            "dur": "0.73", 
            "start": "268.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We&#39;re going to use this method\nthat, well, Gauss may have", 
            "dur": "3.96", 
            "start": "268.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "used to solve his problem.", 
            "dur": "2.16", 
            "start": "272.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But we were adding the numbers\n1 to 1 million.", 
            "dur": "2.12", 
            "start": "275.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But we weren&#39;t adding\nthe numbers.", 
            "dur": "2.92", 
            "start": "277.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I threw in a twist.", 
            "dur": "2.1", 
            "start": "280.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We were adding all the digits\nof the numbers.", 
            "dur": "2.73", 
            "start": "282.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So let&#39;s just write out\nthe numbers first.", 
            "dur": "1.29", 
            "start": "284.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;ll start with 1.", 
            "dur": "1.43", 
            "start": "286.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Then I&#39;ll have 2,\nand 3, and 4.", 
            "dur": "3.59", 
            "start": "287.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m going to skip a few.", 
            "dur": "1.66", 
            "start": "291.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then we&#39;ll go to the end.", 
            "dur": "1.44", 
            "start": "292.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s go to something like\n999,995, 999,996--", 
            "dur": "10", 
            "start": "294.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "getting there--", 
            "dur": "0.55", 
            "start": "304.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "999,999.", 
            "dur": "2.52", 
            "start": "304.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And let&#39;s have 1,000,000.", 
            "dur": "3.154", 
            "start": "307.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There we go.", 
            "dur": "0.976", 
            "start": "310.554"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Right.", 
            "dur": "0.62", 
            "start": "311.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So we were going to add up\nall the digits, though.", 
            "dur": "2.18", 
            "start": "312.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, how about this?", 
            "dur": "2.35", 
            "start": "314.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s just start with the 0.", 
            "dur": "1.35", 
            "start": "316.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m going add on the 0.", 
            "dur": "0.8", 
            "start": "318.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I didn&#39;t say that before,\nbut let&#39;s add on a 0", 
            "dur": "2.25", 
            "start": "318.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "there at the front.", 
            "dur": "0.59", 
            "start": "321.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If I use pairs, 0 paired\nup with 999,999--", 
            "dur": "9.196", 
            "start": "321.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "if you add those together, you\nget this number, 999,999.", 
            "dur": "7.604", 
            "start": "330.866"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you try this pair, we get\nthe same answer, of course.", 
            "dur": "3.92", 
            "start": "338.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And 2 plus this one.", 
            "dur": "3.05", 
            "start": "342.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And do 3 and 999,996.", 
            "dur": "4.635", 
            "start": "345.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And 4 with 999,995.", 
            "dur": "4.175", 
            "start": "350.075"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And all those pairs equal\nthe same thing.", 
            "dur": "2.66", 
            "start": "354.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now if all those pairs equal the\nsame thing, we can now add", 
            "dur": "2.55", 
            "start": "356.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "up these digits.", 
            "dur": "1.84", 
            "start": "359.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this gives me-- what\ndoes this give?", 
            "dur": "1.94", 
            "start": "361.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "9 plus 9 plus 9 plus\n9 plus 9 plus 9?", 
            "dur": "2.786", 
            "start": "363.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "54.", 
            "dur": "1.629", 
            "start": "366.026"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And how many pairs\nhave I made?", 
            "dur": "2.065", 
            "start": "367.655"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Half a million.", 
            "dur": "1.78", 
            "start": "369.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Times half a million.", 
            "dur": "3.98", 
            "start": "371.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Which is equal to--", 
            "dur": "1.71", 
            "start": "375.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it&#39;s actually equal\nto 27 million.", 
            "dur": "4.33", 
            "start": "377.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So all the digits added up to 27\nmillion, except I have left", 
            "dur": "3.79", 
            "start": "381.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "out my 1,000,000 there.", 
            "dur": "2.13", 
            "start": "385.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I didn&#39;t add that in\nmy pair, did I?", 
            "dur": "2.27", 
            "start": "387.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So let&#39;s add up up those\ndigits, too.", 
            "dur": "1.73", 
            "start": "389.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That is 1.", 
            "dur": "2.28", 
            "start": "391.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So we add that on.", 
            "dur": "1.3", 
            "start": "393.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so the answer is, adding\nall the numbers--", 
            "dur": "2.75", 
            "start": "395.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "all the digits of the numbers--\nfrom 1 to 1 million", 
            "dur": "3.46", 
            "start": "397.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is 27,000,001, using\nGauss&#39;s trick.", 
            "dur": "7.226", 
            "start": "401.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MALE SPEAKER: Now at this point,\nyou can go wild, right?", 
            "dur": "2.624", 
            "start": "408.456"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How many-- how many arrows\ndo you want?", 
            "dur": "2.07", 
            "start": "411.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the next one, let&#39;s say we\ndid 3 to the power of, to the", 
            "dur": "3.39", 
            "start": "413.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "power of, to the power--or\narrow, arrow, arrow, or", 
            "dur": "2.245", 
            "start": "416.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "whatever you want\nto call this.", 
            "dur": "2.375", 
            "start": "418.785"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "3--", 
            "dur": "1.13", 
            "start": "421.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "well that, that--", 
            "dur": "1.25", 
            "start": "422.29"
        }
    ], 
